values:
I haven't updated this thing in...years...but greatestjournal shut down, and honestly I like writing. It gets crap out of my system. Sometimes I regret it. I look back at old journal entries and realize how stupid I was. I wrote paragraphs after paragraphs on "love". Undying, relentless, hurtful love. In retrospect, it all looks like nonsense. Pure nonesense. And what bothers me the most is that it goes against everything I am. Conclusion, no more sappy love entries. And a disclaimer. Should I ever feel horridly and have to vent, please (cosita) don't hold it against me. I've always felt journals should have names, mine will be cosita. Coincidentally Gary's nickname but I supposed he is somewhat my journal also so it is fitting. I'm bored and I feel purpose-less. I don't know what my parents did to make me feel so guilty whenever I am not being productive, but whatever it was, they did it well. I never get to relax. I spend my relaxing time thinking about the things I should be doing and my productive time wanting to relax. It's quite the conundrum, maybe its all a matter of scheduling but I've always felt that to be such a waste of time. Scheduling is what I do when I'm tired and want to relax but still feel productive. I feel lonely, also. I never want my emotions to get in the way of my life, but I suppose in one way or another they always do. Sometimes they propell me to be better, sometimes they hold me back. And it feels awful when I (unwillingly) give them a part but I don't think it should. After all, they are a part of me. Everyone has the right to feel. How come the founding fathers didn't include that in their stupid declaration of independence. You have the right to pursue happiness, whatever the fuck that means, but you don't have a right to feel your emotions. Maybe its all one and the same. 
I think I should distance myself from Gary. Its not cause I still have feelings for him or cause I'm afraid, none of that; its cause I know the friendship is off balance. He has a partner, I don't. Therefor, even as a friend, he means more to me than I to him. And thats bad. It's funny...when we're little they give us all that nonesense about giving without thinking of what you're getting in return. In reality, its bullshit. In the real world, no matter how much you want to give, you need to watch your back. It's not about selfishness, its self protection. 
In a relationship, even if you don't care about receiving as much as you desire to give, you need to be careful. Because receiving is an indication that the person you're giving to wants it and deserves it. That the person wont hurt you. Again, not a matter of selfishness at all. 
But even then, no matter how much attention you pay, its all bullshit. Because nothing is stable, nothing stays the same a whole lifetime. Nothing stays the same a whole day for crying outloud! Sometimes I'll wake up and look in the mirror and think that I'm okay. I'm decent looking, relatively intelligent, and fairly accomplished. Maybe I'm the most beautiful or intelligent, but I'm a pretty decent package, I tell myself. Then I go out and when I come back in and undress, I want to cry. Cellulite glares at me, my breasts sag, my stomach makes me feel deformed, my face is too round, I realize I haven't done all I could in school, I feel lonely, etc. Everything changes within the span of 5 hours, maybe. And I could never, till this day, understand why. I love lists. I've kept them about almost anything at some point or another in my life. Things I (dis)liked in others, books, movies, words, likes/dislikes, pet peeves, goals...all my lists are pretty stable. That's why they can be put into ink. But I could never make a list about the things i (dis)like in myself.  It seems to always be changing, to never be concrete. I think all I know about myself is my reaction towards nouns (people/things/events). For example: 
I like cheese, wine, coffee, dark chocolate, hot dogs, bread
I like cold milk with coffee and special K strawberry cereal
I like knowing random facts, like that Dr. Kellog was trying to invent a food so bland it would kill sexual appetite 
I like history, politics, and things to do with people and what makes us people, not animals
I do believe in peace, in making a difference, in ideals, in virtues, and in the value of mankind despite himself.
I definitely like sex. 
I always like the exposition. Getting to know a character, a person, a place. That's the best. I hate endings, I don't like goodbyes.
I run. Always. When I need to shut up, I'm full of words and attitude but if the ocassion calls for it, I never ever confront. And when I go back to do it, of course, its too late. 
I HATE feeling pathetic. I don't admire emotional people.
And I love the fact that I can google anything.
I think wine glasses and shoes are some of the msot sensual things in the world. 
When I dress differently, when I try too hard, when I put together random outfits I've never worn before; its usually cause I don't want to be myself that day.
When I find a person who cares enough to get to know me, to know every little detail on this list, I will always keep him by my side.
I find observation one of the greatest virtues--and one I rarely possess.

I'm tired...and not that interesting.

Graduation was yesterday and it was really awesome. Hahaha to the idiots that didn't go (ex: Ralfy, Javy, Ryne!). I got the FCAT thing for Math. Congratulaions to me. And I'm finally a freshman. woo hoo. lol. Lucky me[at] (get it [meat]). 
Afterwards we went to Olive Garden (Andrea, Shorty, Vanessa, Gio, and families). We had a nice time. None of the young people ate. lol. And we didn't get to drink wine though we were the ones celebrating. And in the parcking lot we screem "We're freshmans!" really really loud. Aren't we cool. lol. Everybody laughed at us. That should eliminate most embarrasing moments of the year. How great. And yeah. Then we went home. Me and Gio argued about his schooling throughout the whole night but w/e thats private. 
So yeah;

CONGRATULATIONS 8TH GRADE CLASS OF 05
GRADUATES IN 09!!!!!!!
WOOO HOOO!
OFICIALLY FRESHMAN
